post_text:
The City of Vidalia is aware of the Facebook posts that have been circulating throughout social media regarding the three planned protests beginning today through Sunday.

The City has a permit procedure in place that it requires by ordinance and has to be approved by City Council. The City has not received any permit requests to be reviewed by City Council.

We are in recognition of a Community Gathering that will be taking place Saturday morning, June 6th, at 9:00 am at the City Stage hosted by several religious leaders in our community. The event's purpose is to promote solidarity and togetherness in our community.

We encourage citizens and business owners alike to support our community in its efforts to stand together in unity.
Please share.

post_text:
The City of Vidalia has reached a 54% response rate with the 2020 Census. To compare with the surrounding area and demonstrate how well Vidalia is responding, the National response is 58.6%; Georgia Self-Response is 54.7%; Toombs County Self-Response is 45.1; City of Lyons is 42.1% and Santa Claus is 61.5%.

GREAT JOB VIDALIA!! Thank you for taking the time to respond to your Census and, please, if you have not responded to your Census, take the time to do so. The responses to this Census will determine the level of funding our City can receive from the Federal / State Governments. Every person counts!

Due to the COVID-19 and in accordance with guidance of Governor Brian Kemp, Vidalia City Hall has TEMPORARILY closed all interior access to the public, but will remain available to service our customers by phone or online. We encourage our customers to use one of the following options to pay bills: Website @ www.vidaliaga.gov. We have suspended the fee for using your credit or debit card. Mail your check to us. Use the drop box located at the front door. Set up monthly drafts of your account with us. If your only option is cash or you are a new customer then please call us at 537-7661 for instructions.

Again, this is a temporary decision during this difficult time. Our goal is to protect our staff and our customers alike. We thank you for your cooperation.

The Pal Theatre
March 16 at 4:08 PM ¬∑

Today, a very difficult decision was made to postpone all scheduled events at The Pal Theatre March 16th - 29th. At this time, we are working to reschedule all of the events, but there are many moving parts to all of this, so please be patient as we contact everyone involved with each event. We hope all the shows will go on, but patience, grace, and understanding are appreciated today and always.

We are excited to announce that we have already rescheduled the ‚ÄúLiverpool Legends‚Äù show. The new show date is Tuesday, May 26, 2020 at 7pm. The movie Play Mobile has been rescheduled for April 3rd and 4th. ALL PRE-SALE TICKETS FOR LIVERPOOL CAN BE USED FOR NEW SHOW DATE.

We are anticipating more changes, so please stay updated by going to our Facebook page, The Pal Theatre or our website at thepaltheatre.com. As always we thank you for your support and understanding in this time of unexpected issues.

Facts about home clothes dryer fires

2,900 home clothes dryer fires are reported each year and cause an estimated 5 deaths, 100 injuries, and $35 million in property loss.

Failure to clean the dryer (34 percent) is the leading cause of home clothes dryer fires.

More home clothes dryer fires occur in the fall and winter months, peaking in January.

The City of Vidalia, Georgia Police Department
January 30 at 3:07 PM ¬∑

Please join us in welcoming our newest Officer, Alejandra Abarca.

Officer Abarca was raised in Toombs County and wants to be an example in the hispanic community. She wants to show others that with hard work and determination one can achieve their goals. Officer Abarca attended the GPSTC Police Academy in Tifton in a pre-service status, meaning she was not sponsored by a law enforcement agency.

We are glad she chose the Vidalia Police Department to start her career in public safety, and look forward to seeing her service to the community. Congratulations Officer Abarca!

NEW YEAR WEEK TRASH PICK UP:
Republic Services will be closed on Wednesday, January 1st. The regularly scheduled pick up on Wednesday will be picked up on Thursday. The regularly scheduled Thursday route will be picked up on Thursday also. There will be an extra truck in the City of Vidalia picking up residential trash on Thursday and Friday. The Friday schedule will remain the same. Recycling will be picked up on Thursdayand if necessary, on Friday. If any residential/recycling trash is not picked up on Thursday as scheduled, please leave your cart by the road and it will be picked up on Friday. The trucks will begin their routes very early so PLEASE HAVE YOUR CART BY THE ROAD WEDNESDAY NIGHT if you are scheduled for a Thursday pickup. PLEASE HAVE YOUR CART BY THE ROAD THURSDAY NIGHT if you are scheduled for a Friday pickup. The regular schedule will resume following this holiday week. Thank you for your cooperation during this holiday season.

Great news! We have decided to extend our Cancer Awareness Campaign through the month of November. We would like to encourage everyone to be proactive by getting screened early and getting screened often.
We have a limited amount of Breast Cancer Awareness shirts left. Sizes S through 3X are available for $15.00 each. All proceeds benefit local Cancer Awareness groups. If you would like to join us in raising awareness by getting "Fired up for a Cure" come by Fire Station 2 (302 West Pine St.) to purchase your shirt(s) OR you can call us at 912-537-4388 OR you can email us at: briansikes25@bellsouth.net, if you are a local business and would like to place a group order, please feel free to complete the form below and email it.Thank you in advance!
